Four siblings were on Saturday, killed by a speeding BMW vehicle at Uselu motor park, Benin City, Edo State as they tried to cross the Benin-Lagos Highway, leading to commotion in the city. Angry youths in the area set the BMW ablaze, but police intervened to stop them lynching the driver. The state Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Chidi Nwabuzor who confirmed the accident said police was at the site to maintain law and order. The Edo State Sector Commander of the Federal Road Safety Corp, Anthony Oko, who also confirmed the accident, said he is yet to get detail of the accident as his men are still on rescue operation.